abstract: Saudi Arabia's crude oil exports rose to 7.898 million barrels per day in March, from 7.350 million barrels per day in February, highest level since 2005.
lead_paragraph: Saudi Arabia’s crude oil exports rose in March to their highest in almost a decade, data showed on Monday, a sign of unexpectedly strong global demand as the top oil exporter increased its output.

headline.main: Saudi Arabia Oil Exports Rose to Highest Levels Since 2005
